snippet.textDisplay: Eating wild animal is cruel and dangerous & banning it is the right way. HOWEVER I found that this video was preoccupied by buzz words such as 'rich & powerful' & 'strong lobby capability'. I would prefer a rational and evidence based way of thinking. For instance, The 1st confirmed case don't even have contact history with the condemned wet market. There might be very different ways that virus get evolved and transmitted to human, and such risk factors may even be present in every corner of the world. I pray that this pandemic will not mark an resurgence of 'yellow peril' theory and we could finally decode the entire process by which the virus evolve and transmitted to human.

snippet.textDisplay: Wet farms should be made illegal or at least very strict guidelines imposed especially given the recent events. If records prove that the inception of most viruses comes from these so called “wet” farms then why are they still continuing to serve the elite exotic animals (that are already under threat!) just for their own selfish pleasure, whilst the rest of us in the world are suffering these preventable diseases. Something has to be done or expect more “unknown” viruses creeping up in the future.
